<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">
    <title>Striker Rolebook</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Striker</h1>
    <p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-pagination:none"><span style="font-family:Arial;font-weight:bold;language:en-GB;mso-ansi-language:
en-GB;mso-ligatures:none" lang="en-GB">NAME:</span><span style="language:en-GB;
mso-ansi-language:en-GB;mso-ligatures:none" lang="en-GB"><span style="mso-tab-count:1"><span

            style="font-family: Arial;">&nbsp;<input name="Name" type="text"></span>
        </span></span><span style="font-family:Arial;font-weight:bold;language:en-GB;mso-ansi-language:en-GB;mso-ligatures:none"

        lang="en-GB">PRONOUNS:&nbsp;</span><span style="language:
en-GB;mso-ansi-language:en-GB;mso-ligatures:none" lang="en-GB"><input name="Pronouns"

          type="text"></span></p>
    <table style="width: 270px; height: 49px;" border="0">
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td style="width: 100px;"><strong>Vitality:<br>
              <input name="Vitality" size="5" type="search"><br>
            </strong></td>
          <td><br>
          </td>
          <td style="width: 100px;"><strong>Experience:<br>
              <input name="Experience" size="5" type="text"><br>
            </strong></td>
          <td><br>
          </td>
          <td style="width: 100px;"><strong>Tenacity:<br>
              <input name="Tenacity" size="5" type="text"><br>
            </strong></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p><span style="language:en-GB;mso-ansi-language:en-GB;mso-ligatures:none" lang="en-GB">You
        hit hard, taking out enemy champions and defences before they can react.
        While you aren’t as tough as a defender, you can overwhelm the enemy and
        be out of there before they can hit back. Strikers cover a wide range of
        warriors, from soldiers to assassins to fearless gladiators.</span></p>
    <p> </p>
    <p><span style="language:en-GB;mso-ansi-language:en-GB;mso-ligatures:none" lang="en-GB">Y</span>ou
      will need to pick a name for your Striker. Then pick their pronouns. Then
      choose one from each line below or write your own:</p>
    <p> Hair: Long braided hair, wild Mohawk, shaved head, <input name="Hair" size="8"

        type="text"> hair<br>
      Clothing: Black stealth gear, light armour, concealing cloak, <input name="Clothing"

        size="8" type="text"><br>
      Look: Grizzled veteran, flamboyant acrobat, cold professional, <input name="Look"

        size="8" type="text"></p>
    <p></p>
    <p>You start with the below stats. </p>
    <p> </p>
    <p> </p>
    <p> </p>
    <table>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Stat</strong></td>
          <td><strong>Start</strong></td>
          <td><strong>Levelled up (Max 6)</strong></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>FORT</strong></td>
          <td>2</td>
          <td><input type="text"></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>REF</strong></td>
          <td>3</td>
          <td><input type="text"></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>WIL</strong></td>
          <td>2</td>
          <td><input type="text"></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>STR</strong></td>
          <td>2</td>
          <td><input type="text"></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>SHO</strong></td>
          <td>2</td>
          <td><input type="text"></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>UT</strong></td>
          <td>1</td>
          <td><input type="text"></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td colspan="3"><strong>Secondary Stats</strong></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>VIT</strong></td>
          <td>10</td>
          <td><input type="text"></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>TEN</strong></td>
          <td>10</td>
          <td><input type="text"><br>
          </td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>Then Choose Two:</p>
    <table style="width: 232px; height: 4px;" border="0">
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td style="width: 87.65px;"><input name="FORT" type="checkbox">&nbsp;+1
            SHO<br>
            <input name="+1 STR" type="checkbox"> +1 STR <br>
          </td>
          <td style="width: 134.35px;"><input name="+2 VIT" value="+2 VIT" type="checkbox">+2
            VIT<br>
            <input name="+2 TEN" type="checkbox"> +2 TEN<br>
          </td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p></p>
    <p>Then choose your signature weapon (choose 1):<br>
      <input name="Weapon" type="checkbox"> <strong>Dual Melee:</strong> <em>4+FORT
        Damage </em>(Defensive [Melee] 1. Attacks are set back twice. However,
      it hits and deals damage on a Success or a Perk. With both a Success and a
      Perk, it deals double damage)<br>
      <input name="Weapon" type="checkbox"> <strong>Dual Ranged: </strong><em>6
        damage </em>(short range. Attacks are set back twice. However, it hits
      and deals damage on a Success or a Perk. With both a Success and a Perk,
      it deals double damage)<br>
      <input name="Weapon" type="checkbox"> <strong>Long-Ranged Weapon: </strong><em>10
        damage </em>(Long range,&nbsp; Prepare 1/1, AP 1)<br>
      <input name="Weapon" type="checkbox"> <strong>Medium-Ranged Weapon and
        backup: </strong><em>8 Damage </em>(Medium range, AP 1) and 3+FORT
      Damage (Melee)<br>
      <input name="Weapon" type="checkbox"> <strong>Light Melee weapon and
        shield:</strong> <em>6+FORT Damage </em>(Defensive [Melee] 2) </p>
    <p> </p>
    <p> </p>
    <p>Then, choose one starting Trait:<br>
      <strong><input name="Trait" type="radio">Deadly Speed:</strong> Thanks to
      training, magic or a monstrous form, you are able to move with
      preternatural swiftness. If you want to move into or out of Melee range
      with another character, you don’t need to use an Action.<br>
      <strong><input name="Trait" type="radio">Rivalry: </strong>Someone on the
      enemy team is your rival. Before the start of the game, choose an enemy
      Champion. Any rolls you make that are in direct opposition to that
      Champion are Pulled Forward once. However, any time your rival beats you
      on a roll, they restore 1 Tenacity.<br>
      <strong><input name="Trait" type="radio">Vampiric Blows:</strong> Whenever
      your roll a Perk on a Strike attack against a non-Fortification character,
      you may use it to recover d4 Vitality.</p>
    <p> </p>
    <p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-pagination:none;margin-bottom:1.0pt"><strong>Abilities</strong></p>
    You start the game with two abilities from the list below:<strong><br>
      <input type="checkbox"> Backup Weapon: </strong>Pick another weapon on
    the Signature Weapon list to also use.<strong></strong><strong><br>
      <input type="checkbox"> Bloodrush:</strong> Whenever you slay an enemy
    character, tick off a Bloodrush box. Your attacks deal extra damage equal to
    your ticked Bloodrush boxes. When you respawn, untick all your Bloodrush
    boxes.
    <p style="text-align: center;"><input type="checkbox"><input type="checkbox"><input

        type="checkbox"><input type="checkbox"> <input type="checkbox"><input type="checkbox"><input

        type="checkbox"><input type="checkbox"> </p>
    <p> </p>
    <p><input type="checkbox"><strong> Coordinated Strike:</strong> If you
      attack another character who has already been hit with an attack this
      round, your roll is Pulled Forward once and you score a perk on a 3 or a
      4.<br>
      <input type="checkbox"><strong>Cullmark (Cooldown 7+ <input type="checkbox">):</strong>
      Choose a Champion within Short range. Until the end of the next Round, any
      attacks you make against them are Pulled Forwards once, and your deal an
      additional 2 damage against them.<br>
      <input type="checkbox"><strong>Dual Wielder </strong>[must have a Dual
      weapon as your signature weapon]: Your dual weapon attacks are only Set
      Back once.<br>
      <input type="checkbox">&nbsp;<strong>Lingering Vengeance:</strong> Anyone
      you kill has their next Respawn roll Set Back once.<br>
      <input type="checkbox">&nbsp;<strong>Parry:</strong> If you roll a Perk to
      dodge a Strike attack, you may deal half your melee damage to your
      attacker.<br>
      <input type="checkbox">&nbsp;<strong>Poisoned Weapons (Cooldown 6+ <input

          type="checkbox">):</strong> If you hit a Champion with a Shoot or
      Strike roll, the next roll made to attack them scores a Perk on a 3 or 4.<br>
      <input type="checkbox">&nbsp;<strong>Safe Distance:</strong> If you attack
      a character who is in another Zone to you, you score a Perk on 3 or 4.<br>
      <strong><input type="checkbox">Single Combat (Cooldown 6+ <input type="checkbox">):
        </strong>&nbsp;Use an action to choose an enemy Champion in Short Range.
      Until the end of the next round, all rolls that Champion makes to attack
      another character are Set Back twice. Any rolls you make to attack that
      Champion are Pulled Forward once.<br>
      <input type="checkbox"> <strong>Tetherport (Cooldown 6+ <input type="checkbox">):
        </strong>Use an action to place a tether anywhere within Short range.
      Use an action to teleport back to the tether, but destroy as it you do. If
      the tether is unused by the end of your next turn, or if you place a new
      tether while it is active, it is destroyed. </p>
    <p></p>
  </body>
</html>
